  "prompt": "Does sample period, symbol period in Simulink measured in second?",
  "response": "In Simulink, sample period or symbol period is typically measured in seconds (s). Here are some key points:\n\n1. Sample Period Units:\n- Normally expressed in seconds (s)\n- Can be very small (e.g., 1e-6 s or microseconds)\n- Can be very large depending on the simulation requirements\n\n2. Common Examples:\n- 0.001 s = 1 millisecond\n- 0.00001 s = 10 microseconds\n- 1 s = 1 second\n\n3. Configuration:\n- Set in block parameters\n- Specified as a numeric value representing time duration\n- Can be fixed or variable depending on the model\n\n4. Considerations:\n- Choose based on signal characteristics\n- Ensure adequate resolution\n- Balance between computational complexity and accuracy\n\nExample:\n- Discrete block: Sample time = 0.01 s (10 milliseconds)\n- Signal generation: Period = 0.001 s (1 millisecond)\n\nAlways specify the sample period in seconds when configuring Simulink blocks and systems.",
